\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 12. P. hirsuta} L.,{\i  Sp. Pl.} 609 (1753). Stem 2-10(-15) cm, erect, subglabrous below, lanate above, leafy throughout. Leaves shorter than stem, linear to lanceolate, pinnatifid, with serrate segments. Flowers in a subcapitate, lanate raceme; bracts similar to cauline leaves, exceeding the calyx. Calyx lanate; teeth subequal, serrate or incise-dentate. Corolla 10-13(-15) mm, bright pink, glabrous; upper lip nearly straight, very obtuse, not toothed; lower lip nearly as long as upper. Capsule obliquely ovoid, apiculate, 1½ times as long as calyx. 2n = 16.{\i  Damp, stony tundra, sea-shores and river-banks; calcicole. Arctic Europe.} Fe No Rs (N) Sb Su.
\par

