\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 15. P. verticillata} L.,{\i  Sp. Pl.} 608 (1753). Stems 5-20(-30) cm, erect, glabrous to crispate-hairy. Basal leaves lanceolate, pinnatifid, with ovate, crenate segments; cauline leaves in whorls of (2-)3-4, similar to the basal but with shorter petioles. Flowers in whorls in a dense spike. Bracts lanceolate, often purplish, hirsute, the lower pinnatifid, the upper crenate. Calyx often purplish, hairy only on the veins; teeth short, entire. Corolla 12-18(-20) mm, purplish-red (rarely pink or white), glabrous; tube twice as long as calyx; upper lip almost straight; lobes of lower lip rounded, not ciliate. Capsule narrowly ovoid, apiculate, almost twice as long as calyx. 2n = 12.{\i  Damp mountain grassland or tundra. Arctic and subarctic Russia; mountains of C. & S. Europe.} Al Au Bu Cz Ga Ge ?Gr He Hs It Ju Po Rm Rs (N, C, w).
\par

